<br>
~Rainangel <p><a href="http://www.angelflame.com/ranger.html" target="_blank"><img border="1" src="http://www.angelflame.com/ranger/image/left_banner.jpg" width="249" height="64"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#7c96b9><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub88.ezboard.com/uruuka100.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ruuka100</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 52<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/31/01 10:35:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub88.ezboard.com/fepicheroes73161frm21.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Excited About Thurgadin Armour</span><hr size=1> I was excited about it to, a long time ago, until I got sick of spending 8 hours there and seeing 2 pieces of Corroded drop that 30 people had to share. You are talking an enormous time sink here. By all means lets go again, but I think our raiding time may be better used by raiding the Plane of Growth. Armour drops there are supposed to be about 6 pieces in 8 hours. You are doing a great job also Sarai, and we appreciate your efforts. <br>
<br>
Ruuka , 54th level sleeping Shaman <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#1478A2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub88.ezboard.com/bepicheroes73161.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=elstaf>Elstaf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Orc Pawn</span><br>  Posts: 115<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/1/01 12:21:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub88.ezboard.com/fepicheroes73161frm21.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Excited About Thurgadin Armour</span><hr size=1> Rangers and Druids cant really do the plane of growth can they, being servants of Tunare and all that? What would happen to a wood elf ranger or druid who did a lot of killing on the PoG? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#7c96b9><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub88.ezboard.com/ubenadan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Benadan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 38<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/1/01 12:40:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub88.ezboard.com/fepicheroes73161frm21.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Excited About Thurgadin Armour</span><hr size=1> Elstaf,<br>
Druids and rangers can hunt on PoG. Several of the guides to that zone I have read state that only certain mobs will give the faction hits you must avoid as a member of these classes. it is not difficult to sit those fights out and avoid the faction hits. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#1478A2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub88.ezboard.com/uruuka100.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ruuka100</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 54<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/2/01 7:46:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub88.ezboard.com/fepicheroes73161frm21.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Excited About Thurgadin Armour</span><hr size=1> Ranger , Druid, and I think Paladin armor drops on the second floor of the Plane of Hate. Armor for those 3 classes does not even drop in the POD as I understand it. If my Deity was Tunare I wouldn't kill anything there. Someone might say there are workarounds to the faction hits, but this game has a way of throwing you curves with horrible consequences you didn't foresee. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#7c96b9><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub88.ezboard.com/usladenprismbeam.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sladen Prismbeam</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Polar Bear Cub</span><br>  Posts: 240<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/2/01 12:29:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub88.ezboard.com/fepicheroes73161frm21.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Excited About Thurgadin Armour</span><hr size=1> Hmm, i thought i remembered hearing about how all classes had a PoG drop armor.<br>
<br>
However, im almost certain that some classes do NOT have a drop in PoH, instead its in PoF.  In this way, not allowing the guild to raid PoG makes it so that while 2 classes are no longer in trouble with faction, all classes lose some potential to get a drop on one raid. <p><hr>
